The paper deals with lower bounds for implementing shared registers, which is a problem in distributed computing. Therefore, cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is the most likely sub-category. The problem also involves data structures, so cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is another likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of atomic registers, which falls under cs.PL (Programming Languages). The problem of implementing shared registers is relevant to systems and control theory, which is covered by cs.SY (Systems and Control). Finally, the paper involves lower bounds, which is a topic in computational complexity theory, covered by cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science).
